    "abstract": "HoloLearn is presented as a mixed reality learning environment tailored for individuals with cognitive disabilities. The study explores the use of MR for supporting educational and rehabilitation goals, highlighting how immersive visualizations and tangible interaction can foster engagement and memory. Results from early user evaluations demonstrate the potential of MR to complement traditional interventions and improve accessibility in learning contexts.",
    "citation": "Garzotto, F., Torelli, E., Vona, F., & Aruanno, B. (2018). HoloLearn: Learning through mixed reality for people with cognitive disability. In 2018 IEEE International Conference on Artificial Intelligence and Virtual Reality (AIVR 2018)."
